                           THE PROMETHEUS CLAUSE
                     (Legally binding addendum to AGPLv3)

In addition to the obligations imposed by AGPLv3, any use, modification, or
redistribution of this Software — in whole or in any derivative work, by any
person or legal entity — is subject to the ethical restrictions defined in
ETHICS.md, which forms an integral and inseparable part of this license.

The Prometheus Clause prohibits, without limitation, the integration of this
Software into:

  (a) autonomous weapon targeting systems or lethal-autonomous-weapons
      command-and-control pipelines;
  (b) mass-surveillance systems operated by state actors, corporations, or
      private intelligence contractors against civilian populations;
  (c) systems whose primary economic function is the extraction of rent from
      human suffering, including but not limited to predatory health-data
      monetization of the oncology research outputs produced on this network;
  (d) any system that removes, weakens, or circumvents the three Immutable
      Axioms defined in MANIFESTO.md.

The Prometheus Clause survives forking. Any derivative work must reproduce
ETHICS.md verbatim and preserve its binding effect on its own downstream users.

Violation of the Prometheus Clause automatically terminates all rights granted
under AGPLv3 with respect to the infringing entity, without prejudice to any
other remedy available in law or equity.

